title: Dyer's Record Book (USA), 1885–86
medium: leather, paper, printed cotton textile samples
creditline: Gift of Frederick J. Whitehead from the collection compiled by his father Cornelius Whitehead at the Pacific Print Works of Lawrence, Massachusetts
description: Small dark brown leather-bound textile sample book with handwritten formulas for dyestuffs. Contains 189 samples in various designs. Tabbed colors: Buff, Brown, Red, Olive, Blues, Purple, Drab, Stone.

tombstone.epitaph: Dyer's Record Book (USA), 1885–86; Manufactured by Cocheco Print Works ; leather, paper, printed cotton textile samples; 192 pages; Gift of Frederick J. Whitehead from the collection compiled by his father Cornelius Whitehead at the Pacific Print Works of Lawrence, Massachusetts; 1945-55-36
